sm in  wang had initiated a  billion hostile takeover for the shares of computer sciences corporation csc the washington post reported csc management’s “concern” about the tender offer by alluding to cas ties to foreigners it was a pointed reference to wangs origin and that certain chinese government institutions as well as those in the us europe and elsewhere were ca clients the suggestion was that becoming linked with ca would jeopardize cscs contracts with us government agencies blaming what in his view was a witchhunt with racial motivations wang dropped the tender offer in  a classaction lawsuit accused wang then president kumar and cofounder artzt of wrongly reporting more than  billion in revenue in its    and  fiscal april through march years in order to artificially inflate the stock price a previous stock option set in  specified that a certain number of shares would vest when computer associates shares sustained a target price the benchmark was met in  and the three executives combined received nearly  billion in computer associates stock with wang himself netting  million he had already been the highest paid ceo in the us for the past four years since then at least four other classaction suits were filed against computer associates all of which have named wang specifically and all of which were settled or dismissed without finding any liability on wang’s part as the controversy continued to dog wang even after he returned a portion of the stock award he quit as ceo in  and later resigned as chairman of the board in  kumar resigned as chairman and chief executive in april  following an investigation into the accounting scandal which improperly reported revenue a federal grand jury in brooklyn indicted kumar on fraud charges on september   kumar pleaded guilty to obstruction of justice and securities fraud charges on april   awards and honorsedit on may   wang was honored by the los angeles chinese historical society of southern california in celebrating c