ue unprofitability they found that several league owners underreported their cable broadcast revenue they specifically accused wang of excluding half of the  million paid to the islanders for the  cable broadcast season wang made numerous efforts to build a new arena in nassau county as the veterans memorial coliseum was the secondoldest active arena and the islanders lease ended in  he was the master developer of the lighthouse project a property transformation of the nassau coliseum and surrounding  acres  km the project was to include a fivestar hotel condominiums an athletic complex featuring four ice rinks a basketball facility and a stateoftheart health club that would have served as the islanders’ practice facility and also be open to the public the development would also have included a sports technology center openair plaza and conference center the project was deemed to be too large by town of hempstead supervisor kate murray who made a counterproposal that was about half the size of what wang had originally intended wang balked at murrays proposal and decided to try to finance the building of a new arena for the islanders with public funds rather than paying for it himself as part of the lighthouse project in may  wang along with nassau county started an day campaign for a  million bond to fund a new arena for the islanders on august   the proposal was defeated by a margin of  to  wang has stated that he would not have bought the team if he knew how difficult it would be and would not do so if he could choose again a new york times article detailed wang’s “desperate” attempts to keep the team on long island ultimately however wang was unable to secure a renovated or new arena in uniondale jeff wilpon the coo of major league baseballs new york mets discussed the possibility of buying the islanders from wang and moving them adjacent to the mets home ballpark citi field in flushing queens there were also reports that businessman nelson peltz wanted to buy the islanders from wang and move them to barclays center in brooklyn on october   wang announced that the islanders would move to barclays center in  after the end of their lease at the nassau veterans memorial coliseum in various interviews wang said that “it was brooklyn or out of town” despite the move the franchise will remain named as the new york islanders and they are geographically still on long island in august  the nhl announced that wang had agreed to sell a substantial minority interest in the team to a group of investors and that the group would be transitioning to majority ownership in two years philanthropyedit wang is an active philanthropist and in  established the charles b wang foundation with the goal of donating to numerous charities that focused on bettering the lives of children and the disenfranchised he has worked with such causes as smile train the world childhood foundation the plainview chinese cultural center and the national center for missing and exploited children among others his donation of over  million to the state university of new york at stony brook for the construction of the charles b wang center was at the time the largest in history to a suny school he also funded the expansion of the chinatown health clinic which was renamed the charles b wang community health center as the cofounder and chairman of smile train in  wang originally gave  million to cover all administrative expenses and has remained active in the charity’s efforts to help children with cleft lip and palates in more than  countries one of the more important attributes that wang brought to his ownership of the islanders was to expand their communitybased programs through the islanders children’s foundation which started in  and has become a mainstay the foundation works with children’s health education and youth hockey development charities in  the team created project hope which is focused on developing ice hockey in china wang recruited womens professional hockey player angela ruggiero to the project as well in  wang and his brothers anthony and francis donated a new law school to chinas soochow university in honor of their father kenneth wang and in celebration of the universitys th anniversary it opened officially in  computer associatesedit charles wang and partner russell artzt established computer associates in  guiding the company toward its current standing as one of the largest independent software corporations in the world one year later computer associates became the first enterprise software company to provide multiplatform products foreshadowing its ongoing emphasis on compatibility and integration by  computer associates became the first software company to reach  billion in revenues wang’s tenure as ceo of computer associates was marked by rapid growth frequently as a result of strict hiring practices and high expectations for executives of acquired companies nearly all of cas managers were promoted from within so very few acquired managers were kept newly hired salespeople had some sales experience but not in software it was unusual for a technician to be considered for sales because cas training program was geared toward products instead of professional selling the passfail demarcation was sharp so perceived inadequate sales performance meant termination all told wang engaged in several dozen acquisitions and those acquired facilities were repopulated with ca employees he was also known for his commitment to a familyoriented management style and for promoting several women to management positions in  three years after cas founding wang had installed his older brother tony a onetime corporate lawyer as president and coo tony held the position until his retirement in  to make way for sanjay kumar who joined ca via its  acquisition of archrival uccel corporation in  nancy li charles wangs second wife was named cas chief technology officer cto responding to criticism over his socalled “paternalistic” management style wang has argued that the investment community punished cas stock because of his refusal to override his sense of familial loyalty to avoid the appearance of nepotism in  wang had initiated a  billion hostile takeover for the shares of computer sciences corporation csc the washington post reported csc management’s “concern” about the tender offer by alluding to cas ties to foreigners it was a pointed reference to wangs origin and that certain chinese government institutions as well as those in the us europe and elsewhere were ca clients the suggestion was that becoming linked with ca would jeopardize cscs contracts with us government agencies blaming what in his view was a witchhunt with racial motivations wang dropped the tender offer in  a classaction lawsuit accused wang then president kumar and cofounder artzt of wrongly reporting more than  billion in revenue in its    and  fiscal april through march years in order to artificially inflate the stock price a previous stock option set in  specified that a certain number of shares would vest when computer associates shares sustained a target price the benchmark was met in  and the three executives combined received nearly  billion in computer associates stock with wang himself netting  million he had already been the highest paid ceo in the us for the past four years since then at least four other classaction suits were filed against computer associates all of which have named wang specifically and all of which were settled or dismissed without finding any liability on wang’s part as the controversy continued to dog wang even after he returned a portion of the stock award he quit as ceo in  and later resigned as chairman of the board in  kumar resigned as chairman and chief executive in april  following an investigation into the accounting scandal which improperly reported revenue a federal grand jury in brooklyn indicted kumar on fraud charges on september   kumar pleaded guilty to obstruction of justice and securities fraud charges on april   awards and honorsedit on may   wang was honored by the los angeles chinese historical society of southern california in celebrating chinese americans in sports long island residenceedit wangs oyster bay mansion on the gold coast of long island is located near sagamore hill president theodore roosevelts home see alsoedit chinese americans in new york city referencesedit  charles wang executive profile  biography  businessweek investingbusinessweekcom  retrieved  october    a b c richard sanomir october   an owner with some eyebrowraising moves the new york times   diamos jason july   owner of the islanders dares to be different the new york times   botte peter  new york islanders owner charles wang nassau county officials pitch m arena project  new york daily news articlesnydailynewscom retrieved  june    caldwell dave august   nassau voters reject proposal to fix coliseum new york times retrieved  august    new york islanders owner charles wang regrets buying struggling team  espn sportsespngocom  retrieved    an owner with some eyebrowraising moves httpswwwnytimescom   external link in publisher help  reprints steve hamm charles wangs messy second act bloombergcom retrieved    mennella dan  mets isles talk about arena near citi mlbcom retrieved    hirshon nicholas january   brooklynqueens battle for the islanders team brewing daily news new york   new york islanders following nets to brooklyn espncom retrieved  october    wang wfan summary  it was brooklyn or out of town    brett hoover angela ruggiero ivy   retrieved  april    kenneth wang school of law  ph tuan architect  soochow university suzhou china aasbuaasquaredorg  retrieved    softwares tough guy part  businessweek  retrieved    alex berenson april    guilty pleas expected today in computer associates case the new york times   the package that launched a dozen lawsuits businessweekcom  retrieved    ca to pursue claims against founder charles wang update bloomberg apr